The article discusses how the United States is responding to the devastating earthquakes that have occurred in Turkey and Syria. The author mentions that the administration has been working closely with Turkey, a NATO ally, and has authorized an immediate U.S. response. Senior American officials have reached out to their Turkish counterparts to coordinate assistance efforts. U.S. teams are being deployed to support search and rescue operations and provide aid to those affected by the earthquake. Additionally, humanitarian partners supported by the U.S. are also responding to the destruction in Syria. The article expresses condolences to those who have lost loved ones, and those who have been injured or displaced.